[normal]3.1.
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Reforms to Local Housing Allowance (LHA) introduced from April 2011 included setting the rates at the 30th percentile 
[normal]rather th
[normal]an the median 
[normal]of market rents, 
[normal]capping the maximum LHA rates
[normal], 
[normal]removing the 5
[normal]-bed
[normal] rate
[normal] and no longer allowing claimants to retain any excess of up to £15 a week between the
[normal]ir actual rent and the
[normal] LHA rate.
[normal]  From January 2012, the 
[normal]upper 
[normal]age 
[normal]limit 
[normal]for the LHA 
[normal]shared accommodation rate for single people 
[normal]without dependent children 
[normal]was 
[normal]raised 
[normal]from 25 to 35.
[normal]3.2.
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]For all these reforms, claimants had up to 
[normal]nine 
[normal]months
[normal]’
[normal] transitional protection from their anniversary date, so only started to be affected 
[normal]between January 2012 and 
[normal]December
[normal] 2012
[normal].  The 
[normal]Department is 
[normal]providing
[normal] 
[normal]£40 million in Discretionary Housing Payments
[normal] 
[normal]in 2013/14
[normal] 
[normal]to 
[normal]help
[normal] people 
[normal]make the transition to 
[normal]the 
[normal]LHA 
[normal]reforms.
