[normal]7.1.
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Council Tax Benefit was abolished in April 2013 and replaced with council tax reduction schemes, designed and administered locally. Loca
[normal]lisation means that authorities make decisions as to how they raise revenue through council tax, and gives them a bigger stake in delivering economic growth.
[normal]7.2.
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Council Tax reduction schemes will not form part of Universal Credit, and the award of a reduction
[normal] will have no impact on a claimant's Universal Credit entitlement. However, 
[normal]the Department 
[normal]recognise
[normal]s
[normal] that there are important interactions including impacts on work incentives.
[normal]7.3.
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]The Department has 
[normal]worked with the Department for Communities and Local Govern
[normal]ment 
[normal](DCLG) 
